field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Jazz5, Folk3, Goof1A, Champ4A. Goof and Champ are sputtered Ir(18)Ox. at RT and 400 C, rsptv.
field_data.Removed from vacuum: Goof sputtered yesterday, Champ sputtered today. Jazz5 last used as control 19C01

notes: Goof1 involved a mistake, namely forgetting to open the Reactive Gas valve. It is therefore ~8nm IrOx on ~10 nm Ir on ~5nm Ti on GC. I was quite worried about this mistake diluting the (18)O2, but Goof1A looks good in the theta probe! Champ4 is sputtered today without any significant mistake except a small inturruption when the (18)O2 in the line ran out, and that the middle sample fell into the sputter chamber. It's about 10 nm Ru(18)O2 on ~5nm Ti on GC. Jazz5 is the control, having (I think!) not seen (18)O. --- Jazz5 --- 01... WTF?! There's exchange. I think that I have mislabeled samples or written a wrong sample in the notes file 19C01. Indeed, in 19C01 refers to Jazz5 as "Ir on Ti on Au" ... but the sample that I'm testing now is a GC substrate... Jazz3 is an Au substrate. first electrolyte sample at 2 min, not 1 min. 1 min might in general be too early. Pulled in some air during the 20 min electrolyte sample. .... Ah, shit, actually it was EC-lab programming mistake. It cycled down to 1.2 V vs RHE and back up WHILE I was extracting electrolyte.Also, spilled some of that electrolyte and pippetted it up from the Al foil on the table. link1 02... Folk3. Stupid EC-lab changed CP to 1 uA without asking. Actual control. Just out of ISS. This one looks good. link2 03... Goof1A No exchange! link3 all goes smooth. Few small bubbles, remarkably clean given it's a chipped electrode. 03a... forgot to record OCP 04... Champ4A Stub too loose. Need Teflon tape. Checked conductance through RDE stick. Looks okay. Bad first mount of cell, o-ring had come loose, leaking electrolyte. Some of this electrolyte collected as an OCP dissolution measurement. OCP looks much lower than others. CV indistinguishable from resistor. Maybe there's a crazy tilt. Stupid EC-lab changed CP to 1 uA without asking. Change to 100 uA. Potential lower, O2 signal lower than it should be. Yes, everything just looks crazy tilty.
